Fig. 4
 shows, as an example, overlays of the original FTIR spectra of several locations in the region characteristic for lipids, in root outward epidermis layer (Fig. 4A) and leaf xylem (Fig. 4B) for different treatments. The spectra indicate decrease in band intensity in the root epidermis and leaf xylem for all treatments compared to the control. In order to follow easier changes of different bands, and different treatments we summarized data and show here results in the PCA biplots (Figs. 5–7

), as explained in Material and methods. The insets in Figs. 5–7 represent loading plots of the first two principal components.
